A vintage-style illustrated cross-section of an old wooden filing cabinet with four distinct drawers, each drawer progressively more weathered and dusty from top to bottom. The top drawer is open and glowing with warm golden light, containing fresh crisp papers with visible activity. The second drawer shows papers mid-motion as if being shuffled. The third drawer is closed but pristine, with a slight patina. The bottom drawer is covered in cobwebs and aged wood grain, with antique brass handles tarnished green. The scene is rendered in muted sepia tones with pops of amber and brass, evoking 1940s technical illustration style. Dust motes float in dramatic diagonal light beams cutting across the scene. The cabinet sits on an ornate Persian rug against a backdrop of aged wallpaper with subtle damask patterns.
